==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Escapade
<hw>Es`ca*pade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. Sp.
<ets>escapada</ets> escape, fr. <ets>escapar</ets> to escape; or F., fr.
It. <ets>scappata</ets> escape, escapade, fr. <ets>scappare</ets> to
escape. see <er>Escape</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The fling of a
horse, or ordinary kicking back of his heels; a gambol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 509 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Act by which one breaks loose from the rules of
propriety or good sense; a freak; a prank.</def>
<rj><au>Carlyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Escape</ent>⟦br⟧
